---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — Uuumi"
  description="How Uuumi handles your data. We only collect your email to notify you about our launch."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main class="privacy">
    <div class="container content">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: March 22, 2026</p>

      <section>
        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          Uuumi is operated by Jan Podmolik. If you have any questions about how we handle your data,
          you can reach us at <a href="mailto:info@uuumi.app">info@uuumi.app</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What data we collect</h2>
        <p>
          We collect only your <strong>email address</strong> when you sign up for the Uuumi waitlist.
          That's it — no name, no phone number, no browsing history.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Why we collect it</h2>
        <p>We use your email to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Send you your OG essence claim code after signing up</li>
          <li>Notify you when Uuumi is ready to launch</li>
          <li>Occasionally share product updates and news about Uuumi</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We keep emails to a minimum — no spam, no third-party promotions. Every email you receive will be about Uuumi. You can unsubscribe at any time by contacting us.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Legal basis</h2>
        <p>
          We process your email based on your <strong>explicit consent</strong>, which you give by
          checking the consent checkbox on the waitlist form. You can withdraw your consent at any
          time by contacting us.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Who processes your data</h2>
        <p>Your email is handled by the following services:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Supabase</strong> — stores your email in our database</li>
          <li><strong>Resend</strong> — delivers the welcome email to your inbox</li>
          <li><strong>Google</strong> — analytics and ad measurement via Google Tag Manager (only with your consent)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All services are GDPR-compliant and process data on our behalf.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
          Your email is stored until you request its deletion or until 12 months after Uuumi
          launches — whichever comes first. After that, it's permanently deleted.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>Under GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access the data we hold about you</li>
          <li>Correct any inaccurate data</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Restrict how we process your data</li>
          <li>Export your data (data portability)</li>
          <li>Withdraw your consent at any time</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, email us at
          <a href="mailto:info@uuumi.app">info@uuumi.app</a>. We'll respond within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Cookies &amp; tracking</h2>
        <p>
          We use Google Tag Manager to manage analytics and marketing tags on this website.
          When you first visit, a consent banner asks you to choose which categories of cookies
          you allow. Your choices are saved in your browser's localStorage and respected on
          every subsequent visit.
        </p>
        <p>We categorise cookies as follows:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Necessary</strong> — Required for basic site functionality (theme preference).
            These do not require consent and use localStorage only.</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics</strong> — Help us understand how visitors use the site
            (e.g. Google Analytics). Only activated if you give consent.</li>
          <li><strong>Marketing</strong> — Used to deliver relevant ads and measure campaign
            effectiveness (e.g. Facebook Pixel, TikTok Pixel). Only activated if you give consent.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          You can change your cookie preferences at any time by clicking "Cookies" in the footer.
        </p>
        <p>
          We use Google Consent Mode v2 to ensure that no analytics or marketing
          data is collected until you explicitly opt in. By default, all non-essential cookies
          are denied.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .privacy {
    padding-top: 7rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .updated {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  li {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  a:hover {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
